  I run a Windows XP Pro box and have a recurring error every month or so that crashes me.  Happened again today and takes hours to fix sometimes.  I basically had a completely working system, rebooted, and come back to a blue screen and an error code.  The error always seems to be hovering around the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ntfs.sys</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> file.  I end up reinstalling the OS, which runs fine for a month or two and then it happens again.  I'm getting really tired of losing data and time to this error, and am hoping that someone in this forum is knowledgable about what the problem is or how to finally fix it.  I know some of you folks out there are extremely computer savvy...help!<br>
